        <updateDate>2019-08-20T21:35:16Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Fair Elections Now Act</b></p> <p>This bill establishes the Fair Elections Fund, which shall provide funding to Senate candidates who meet&nbsp;specified conditions and agree to abide by certain requirements, such as limits on types of campaign funding sources and a minimum number of appearances in&nbsp;public debates. The bill also (1) revises provisions related to broadcasts of Senate campaign advertisements, (2) provides a tax credit for individuals who make certain types of Senate campaign contributions, and (3) imposes a tax on certain U.S. government contracts.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
